preemptible VMs can provide up to 80% discount over normal VMs if the workloads are fault-tolerant.  
It proposes running the batch job in a simulation of maintenance events.  
This allows for testing if the job can still run properly even if some VMs get destroyed.  
If the test is successful, preemptible N1 Standard VMs can be used for future jobs.  
Preemptible VMs are significantly cheaper than regular VMs, helping to reduce costs.  

https://cloud.google.com/spot-vms  
